## 2. `.gitignore` (Version Control Cleanup)

This file tells Git which files it should **ignore** and not track or commit to the repository. This is crucial for keeping out temporary files, build artifacts, and executables.

Create this file in the root directory (`QuizGame_CPP/`).

```gitignore
# --------------------
# C++ PROJECT IGNORE FILE
# --------------------

# Executables and build output
# The main executable we compile
QuizGame
QuizGame.exe

# Object files (intermediary compilation files)
*.o
*.obj

# Debug files
*.d

# CMAKE Files (if you choose to use CMake later)
/build
CMakeCache.txt
CMakeFiles/
Makefile
cmake_install.cmake

# IDE specific files (common editors and IDEs)
# Visual Studio
.vs/
*.vcxproj.user
*.suo

# VS Code
.vscode/

# Vim/Nano temporary files
*~